  "source_notes": "Sy Scholfield quotes from ''Bess Of Hardwick: First Lady of Chatsworth'' by Mary S. Lovell (Hachette UK, 4 June 2009):\\n\\n\"She [Bess] became pregnant again almost immediately, and there was some consolation before the year was out when she gave birth to a healthy son. Sir William wrote: 'Henry, my 11th child, and the third by the same woman, was borne of Tuesday at 12 of the clock at night . . . the 17th day of December [1550].\"\\n\\nThe day of the week for 17 December 1550 under the old Julian calendar was Wednesday, therefore he was born at midnight between the 16th and 17th.\\n",
